On October 16, Huang Chunfa, a businessman from Fujian, published a "thank you letter" on his WeChat public account, "thanking" himself for being detained in Shangrao Detention Center in Jiangxi for 5 years.
In the article, the businessman said that his case was clearly investigated by the procuratorate and returned because of insufficient evidence, but in the end he was still prosecuted under some unknown pressure. After being prosecuted, the court still acquitted him, but the detention center refused to grant bail.
The businessman said, "The detention center is good. I don't need to worry about business operations, let alone weight loss. My physical fitness has greatly improved. Such a regular life is really something that billions of assets can't buy. I especially want to invite leaders of the Shangrao Municipal Political and Legal System to come in and eat and live with me for a few years. I guarantee that you will all be in good health and eat delicious food. Leaders of Shangrao, if you don't come now, it will be too late and you won't be able to grab a seat."

October 16 (released), in August this year, the Organization Department and the Ministry of Human Resources and Social Security of Guangdong Province issued a notice announcing that college graduates who have completed the "Three Supports and One Assistance" (supporting medical care, education, agriculture and rural revitalization) will no longer enjoy extra points for the examination. Some local recruitments have even issued recruitment instructions, confirming that the "Three Supports and One Assistance" extra points are valid, but before the exam, it was stopped by the provincial department and notified that candidates could not get extra points.
Many students who chose to participate in the "Three Supports and One Assistance" project two years ago have now ended up with nothing, wasting two years of youth, and it is no longer attractive to find a job in private enterprises, facing the dilemma of unemployment.

content: The farm owner used Gatling fireworks to drive away villagers who stole corn. On the evening of October 15, after a large machine harvested corn in Qishan County, Baoji City, Shaanxi Province, some people went to the field to grab corn. The farm owner drove a pickup truck into the field and set up Gatling fireworks on the truck. The fireworks sprayed at the crowd picking up corn, and the crowd evacuated to the edge of the field. From the video, some of the people were elderly people. The video poster said it was a "helpless move." The video shows that villagers followed the harvester to pick up corn at around 6 o'clock in the morning. Many farmers complained that they worked hard to grow crops, but all the corn that fell on the ground was picked up, and the harvest was affected. "

name: 李老师不是你老师
content: Did the Intel incident originate from the information collected during the development of intelligent driving? On October 16, the Ministry of State Security announced that a domestic company cooperated with a foreign company to carry out research on intelligent driving of automobiles. The test vehicle was integrated with high-tech surveying and mapping equipment, and the data collected was in a private format that the competent industry department could not read with common software. Under the guidance of the foreign party A, the surveying and mapping data was transferred out of the country, which violated the responsibility of confidentiality management of surveying and mapping data. The national security agency investigated the case and punished the company involved and the relevant responsible personnel. It is said that this matter was the cooperation between NavInfo and Mobileye, a subsidiary of Intel, in 2018.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content: On the evening of October 16, NavInfo issued an announcement denying any connection with what was stated in the Ministry of State Security's notice.

content: The second landlord absconded with the money? Recently, in Xitang Huayuan, Hangzhou, Zhejiang, a real estate agency absconded with about 4 million yuan from the landlord and tenant. A staff member of the Xitang Yayuan Community Residents Committee said that the agency signed the contract with the landlord in his personal name and then sublet it to other people. Previously, some landlords in the community contacted the agency because they did not receive the rent when it was due, and found that the phone was not connected. Later, other similar situations occurred. As of now, a total of fifty or sixty tenants have registered in the community. Some tenants have been affected and asked to move out by the landlord. At present, the police station is following up on this matter.

content:
Nezha Auto owes wages? On October 16, a netizen who was certified as an employee of Nezha Auto said on social media that Nezha’s salary was not paid normally last month and the company owed a lot of money to suppliers. He advised everyone to be cautious when buying Nezha Auto. Nezha Auto responded that the salaries of front-line employees have been paid, and the middle and senior management are doing equity optimization and salary structure adjustment. The rights must be confirmed before the IPO, so some salaries are paid a little slower.
In early September this year, some media reported that Chen Rui, CFO (Chief Financial Officer) of Nezha Auto, was exposed to have resigned recently. Former Goldman Sachs (Asia) Managing Director Pan Deng replaced Chen Rui and was responsible for Nezha’s financial work.
